        YOUR_CHOCOBO_REFUSES_TO_PARTAKE_OF_THE                                  = 7363,  -- Your chocobo refuses to partake of the %.
        YOUR_WING_SKILL_IMPROVED_TO                                             = 7364,  -- Your wing skill improved to #!
        ON_NORTHERN_QUON_LIES_THE_WALLED_CAPITAL_OF                             = 7365,  -- On northern Quon lies the walled capital of the Kingdom of San d'Oria.
        HOME_TO_FABLED_WARRIORS_KNOWN_AS_ROYAL_KNIGHTS                          = 7366,  -- Home to fabled warriors known as Royal Knights, she is a land where strength of arms rules over all.
        YET_HER_OBSESSION_WITH_MIGHT_HAS_WIDENED_THE                            = 7367,  -- Yet, her obsession with might has widened the gap between San d'Oria and the advanced industries and economies of its neighbors.
        IT_S_LOCKED_TIGHT                                                       = 7368,  -- It's locked tight.
        PTTHE_FORTRESS_CITY_OF_SAN_D_ORIA_LIES                                  = 7370,  -- PTThe fortress city of San d'Oria lies to the north on the great continent of Quon. The beating heart of an ancient kingdom, it is home to a thousand legends past.
        PTBUT_NOW_HER_REIGN_OF_GLORY_IS_BUT                                     = 7371,  -- PTBut now, her reign of glory is but a memory. Heroes raise shining swords to the heavens no more.
        PTTHE_SUN_HAS_SET_ON_THE_KINGDOM_OF                                     = 7372,  -- PTThe sun has set on the kingdom of knights. An old lion, never to rise again... Thus do some dismiss her now.
        PTYET_YOUNG_ELVAAN_KNIGHTS_STILL_VENTURE_PROUDLY_INTO                   = 7373,  -- PTYet young Elvaan knights still venture proudly into the wilds of Vana'diel, determined to triumph over any foe.
        PTON_THIS_PARTICULAR_DAY_THERE_COMES_A_NEW                              = 7374,  -- PTOn this particular day there comes a new adventurer, ready to make a name for himself/herself] in San d'Oria.
        PTTHE_KING_WISHES_TO_BOLSTER_HIS_RANKS_AND                              = 7375,  -- PTThe king wishes to bolster his ranks, and % has journeyed far to answer the call.
        PTSHOULD_FORTUNE_FAVOR_HIM_HER_BARDS_ACROSS_THE                         = 7376,  -- PTShould fortune favor him/her], bards across the land will sing of his/her] exploits for generations to come.
        PTOF_COURSE_HE_SHE_HAS_ONLY_BEGUN_HIS                                   = 7377,  -- PTOf course, he/she] has only begun his/her] rise to glory. No one can tell what his/her] future holds.
        PTNEVER_BEFORE_HAS_HE_SHE_SET_FOOT_WITHIN                               = 7378,  -- PTNever before has he/she] set foot within the Elvaan capital, but he/she] is resolved to let nothing stand in his/her] way.
        I_SAY_WATCH_WHERE_YOU_RE_GOING                                          = 7379,  -- I say! Watch where you're going!
        OH_A_NEW_RECRUIT_ARE_YOU_THAT_EXPLAINS                                  = 7380,  -- Oh, a new recruit, are you? That explains it!
        WELL_FAR_BE_IT_FROM_ME_TO_CHASTISE                                      = 7381,  -- Well, far be it from me to chastise someone on his/her] first day. Still, as a citizen of San d'Oria, you--
        AH_AVANDALE_WHAT_ARE_YOU_DOING_THERE                                    = 7382,  -- Ah, Avandale! What are you doing there?
        PRINCE_TRION_I_WAS_EXPLAINING_TO_THIS_RECRUIT                           = 7383,  -- Prince Trion, I was explaining to this recruit here about what it means to be a proud citizen of San d'Oria!
        A_NEW_RECRUIT_STRENGTHEN_YOUR_SWORD_ARM_AND                             = 7384,  -- A new recruit? Strengthen your sword arm and your stature as a knight. Thus will you best serve the glory of our great kingdom.
        SAN_D_ORIA_HAS_MORE_THAN_ENOUGH_SOLDIERS                                = 7385,  -- San d'Oria has more than enough soldiers already, brother. Speaking of which, should you not be training them, instead of bothering new recruits with talk of war?
        YOU_ARE_TOO_BOLD                                                        = 7386,  -- You are too bold!
        REALLY_PIEUJE_IS_THAT_ANY_WAY_TO_SPEAK                                  = 7387,  -- Really, Pieuje! Is that any way to speak to your brother?
        I_VE_SAID_THE_TRUTH_NOTHING_MORE_THE                                    = 7388,  -- I've said the truth, nothing more. The ranks of our armies could swell to bursting, and victory would still be far.
        IT_IS_YOUR_HEAD_THAT_IS_SWOLLEN_BROTHER                                 = 7389,  -- It is your head that is swollen, brother. With enough numbers, we could crush the beastmen! And without having to resort to your misguided tactics!
        MY_TACTICS_MISGUIDED_OH_THAT_IS_RICH_TELL                               = 7390,  -- My tactics, misguided? Oh, that is rich! Tell me of the tactics that lost an entire company in Batallia Downs the other day?
        IT_S_GOOD_YOU_RE_SO_FOND_OF                                             = 7391,  -- It's good you're so fond of talking, as I've never seen you wield a sword! Better to shout orders from the rear than reveal your ineptitude in actual combat!
        STOP_YOUR_QUARRELING_BOTH_OF_YOU                                        = 7392,  -- Stop your quarreling, both of you!
        A_DIVIDED_LEADERSHIP_ONLY_CREATES_UNREST_AMONG_THE                      = 7393,  -- A divided leadership only creates unrest among the people, soldier and civilian alike. Surely you are both aware of this?
        OH_I_SUPPOSE_I_WARN_YOU_PIEUJE_TALK                                     = 7394,  -- Oh, I suppose. I warn you, Pieuje, talk to me that way again and I won't be so forgiving.
        GOOD_OLD_TRION_THREATS_OF_VIOLENCE_ARE_HIS                              = 7395,  -- Good old Trion. Threats of violence are his only recourse when a conversation does not go his way. Like a child, he is!
        THEY_ARE_BOTH_LIKE_CHILDREN_QUICK_TO_INSULT                             = 7396,  -- They are both like children, quick to insult and quicker to take offense! Really...
        I_MUST_APOLOGIZE_FOR_THAT_BUT_OURS_IS                                   = 7397,  -- I must apologize for that. But ours is truly a great kingdom, and I expect you to further her glory.
        THOSE_TWO_ARE_A_HANDFUL_BUT_THEY_TRULY                                  = 7398,  -- Those two are a handful, but they truly are the closest of brothers.
        PERHAPS_I_COULD_BE_OF_SERVICE_IS_THERE                                  = 7399,  -- Perhaps I could be of service. Is there anything in particular you'd like to know?
        SOMETHING_YOU_D_LIKE_TO_KNOW_NOTHING_ACTUALLY                           = 7400,  -- Something you'd like to know? Nothing, actually. I'd like to get out of the city. I'd like to do some shopping. Tell me more about adventuring.
        JUST_GOT_HERE_AND_YOU_RE_ACHING_TO                                      = 7401,  -- Just got here and you're aching to leave, eh? Listen, the lands are wild beyond our gates, filled with fiends and their ilk.
        BUT_IF_YOU_MUST_GO_TAKE_THOSE_STAIRS                                    = 7402,  -- But if you must go, take those stairs, head for Northern San d'Oria, then go out Ranperre Gate. You'll need to go down Laborman's Way, then take a right to get to the gate.
        IF_YOU_NEED_ANY_HELP_WITH_DIRECTIONS_ASK                                = 7403,  -- If you need any help with directions, ask those around you. Our citizens are friendly, for the most part.
        WAIT_WAIT_ONE_MORE_THING_IF_SOMEONE_AIDS                                = 7404,  -- Wait, wait! One more thing. If someone aids you, be sure to show them your gratitude. That is all.
        IF_YOU_WANT_TO_BUY_WEAPONS_OR_OTHER                                     = 7405,  -- If you want to buy weapons or other supplies, just ask one of the merchants in town.
        AHH_RECRUITS_DON_T_KNOW_WHICH_WAY_TO                                    = 7406,  -- Ahh, recruits... Don't know which way to hold a sword and you think you're ready for adventures. Well, what would you like to know?
        YOU_NEED_TO_GO_TO_THE_NOVICE_S                                          = 7407,  -- You need to go to the Novice's Hall. You'll find it in Southern San d'Oria.
        WHAT_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_KNOW_HELPING_PEOPLE                              = 7408,  -- What would you like to know? Helping people. Hunting monsters. Making easy money. Working for my country.
        AH_A_COMMENDABLE_CHOICE_COME_TO_THINK_OF                                = 7409,  -- Ah, a commendable choice! Come to think of it, there was a lady in front of a house on Pikeman's Way. She may be in need of assistance.
        AH_A_COMMENDABLE_CHOICE_HMM_YES_COME_TO                                 = 7410,  -- Ah, a commendable choice! Hmm, yes... Come to think of it, there was a lady just down those stairs. She may be in need of assistance.
        AHH_RECRUITS_DON_T_KNOW_YOUR_OWN_LIMITS                                 = 7411,  -- Ahh, recruits... Don't know your own limits until a fiend beats it into your head for you. Very well. How about gathering some hides?
        FROM_NORTHERN_SAN_D_ORIA_PASS_THROUGH_VICTORY                           = 7412,  -- From Northern San d'Oria, pass through Victory Arch to enter Southern San d'Oria. There you'll find the Tanners' Guild. They need hides every now and then.
        IF_YOU_HAVE_TROUBLE_FINDING_THE_TANNERS_GUILD                           = 7413,  -- If you have trouble finding the Tanners' Guild, just ask around.
        EASY_MONEY_EH_TYPICAL_OF_A_NEW_RECRUIT                                  = 7414,  -- Easy money, eh? Typical of a new recruit. I cannot promise ease, but try the lumberyard in Northern San d'Oria. Should be enough work for you there.
        GO_UP_THOSE_STAIRS_THERE_TO_GET_TO                                      = 7415,  -- Go up those stairs there to get to Northern San d'Oria. You'll find the lumberyard near the top.
        AH_A_COMMENDABLE_CHOICE_HEAD_TO_ANY_CITY                                = 7416,  -- Ah, a commendable choice. Head to any city gate and inquire at the gatehouse. They'll give you work befitting your rank.
        HERE_TAKE_THIS_IT_S_GIVE_IT_TO                                          = 7417,  -- Here, take this. It's %. Give it to Teilsa at the bottom of the staircast in Northern San d'Oria. She'll help you out.
        TO_GIVE_ITEMS_TO_OTHERS_SELECT_TRADE_FROM                               = 7418,  -- To give items to others, select Trade from the main menu. Don't you forget it!
        WHAT_A_PICKPOCKET_WELL_I_DID_SEE_A                                      = 7419,  -- What? A pickpocket? Well, I did see a strange woman run to Northern San d'Oria. But I didn't see her steal anything.
        ALL_RIGHT_THEN_I_AM_READY_TO_EAT                                        = 7420,  -- All right, then! I am ready to eat!
        WELCOME_WHAT_LL_IT_BE                                                   = 7421,  -- Welcome. What'll it be?
        I_CLEARLY_HEARD_THAT_THE_KNIGHTS_WERE_PLANNING                          = 7422,  -- I clearly heard that the knights were planning a strike on those Ghelsba Orcs. Whatever came of that?
        WELL_HOW_COULD_THE_TWO_PRINCES_POSSIBLY_ORGANIZE                        = 7423,  -- Well, how could the two princes possibly organize a raid? They can't even agree on the color of the sky!
        THEN_IS_IT_TRUE_THAT_THE_FIRST_PRINCE                                   = 7424,  -- Then, is it true that the first prince to quell the Orcs of Ghelsba will inherit the Kingdom?
        BAH_SIMPLY_TAKING_GHELSBA_WON_T_MAKE_ANYBODY                            = 7425,  -- Bah. Simply taking Ghelsba won't make anybody king.
        AYE_BUT_HE_D_BE_A_STEP_CLOSER                                           = 7426,  -- Aye, but he'd be a step closer to the throne! Still, it must be in their blood to quarrel.
        IT_S_BEEN_TWENTY_YEARS_SINCE_THE_GREAT                                  = 7427,  -- It's been twenty years since the Great War, and the king is old. His little princes have grown into men, now...
        YET_I_HEAR_THEY_BICKER_OVER_WHICH_WILL                                  = 7428,  -- Yet I hear they bicker over which will be king. A sadder fate has never befell a kingdom, if it's true.
        WHO_KNOWS_AND_THEY_WERE_SUCH_GOOD_BROTHERS                              = 7429,  -- Who knows? And they were such good brothers in their youth.
        AYE_TIS_TRUE_THAT_SAN_D_ORIA_JOINED                                     = 7430,  -- Aye, 'tis true that San d'Oria joined Windurst, Bastok, and Jeuno in war twenty years ago. We slew the Shadow Lord, and drove back his hordes!
        I_SAY_WE_BUT_WHAT_DID_THE_ABSENT                                        = 7431,  -- I say we, but what did the absent-minded Windurstians and granite-licking Bastokers do? Nothing! And don't get me started on those upstart fishermen from Jeuno!
        OUR_KNIGHTS_TRIUMPHED_AGAINST_DARKNESS_THAT_DAY_SAN                     = 7432,  -- Our knights triumphed against darkness that day. San d'Oria saved this world from the clutches of the Shadow Lord!
        SOON_OUR_GREAT_KINGDOM_WILL_BRING_PEACE_TO                              = 7433,  -- Soon, our great kingdom will bring peace to this land! Fight with me, my brothers, until that glorious day has come!
        EGADS_I_M_HUNGRY_I_FEEL_FAINT                                           = 7434,  -- Egads, I'm hungry! I feel faint...
        BRING_MEAT_ANY_MEAT_I_SAY_I_M                                           = 7435,  -- Bring meat! Any meat, I say! I'm just back from a long march, and I hunger!
        I_AM_TERRIBLY_SORRY_SIR_WE_VE_RUN                                       = 7436,  -- I am terribly sorry, sir. We've run out of meat, you see--
        OUT_OF_MEAT_WELL_I_I_GUESS_THERE                                        = 7437,  -- Out of meat! Well I...I guess there's no helping that now, is there? What else have you got?
        WE_HAVE_THE_USUAL_I_LL_BRING_IT                                         = 7438,  -- We...have the usual. I'll bring it right out.
        BY_ALTANA_NOT_BEANS_AGAIN                                               = 7439,  -- By Altana! Not beans again...
        I_M_AFRAID_SO                                                           = 7440,  -- I'm afraid so...
        PLEASE_I_VE_HAD_NAUGHT_BUT_BEANS_FOR                                    = 7441,  -- Please! I've had naught but beans for weeks!
        AND_A_BELLY_FULL_OF_BEANS_DOESN_T                                       = 7442,  -- And a belly full of beans doesn't satisfy.
        HMM_IF_ONLY_I_HAD_FIVE_I_COULD                                          = 7443,  -- Hmm... If only I had five %, I could make something for him.
        BY_THE_GODDESS_NOT_BEANS_AGAIN_OH_ANYTHING                              = 7444,  -- By the Goddess, not beans again. Oh, anything...anything but beans.
        WHAT_I_DIDN_T_ASK_FOR_THIS                                              = 7445,  -- What? I didn't ask for this.
        WHY_THESE_ARE_FINE_HAND_THEM_TO_THE                                     = 7446,  -- Why, these are fine %! Hand them to the chef, friend, right away!
        WHAT_S_THIS_I_DON_T_NEED_THIS                                           = 7447,  -- What's this? I don't need this!
        ALTANA_BLESS_YOU_I_CAN_FINALLY_MAKE_MY                                  = 7448,  -- Altana bless you! I can finally make my customers some %! Give me that meat, then, and I'll make sure you're paid.
        YOU_RECEIVE_A_PAYMENT_OF_30_GIL                                         = 7449,  -- You receive a payment of 30 gil.
        ADVENTURER_YOU_BROUGHT_THE_MEAT_EH_I_THANK                              = 7450,  -- Adventurer! You brought the meat, eh? I thank you from the bottom of my stomach!
        LET_ME_SHARE_A_TIDBIT_OF_KNOWLEDGE_WITH                                 = 7451,  -- Let me share a tidbit of knowledge with you. It might come in handy.
        YOU_KNOW_WHAT_THEY_SAY_ABOUT_A_GOOD                                     = 7452,  -- You know what they say about a good meal? Well, it's true that food can give you a real boost. Try a few dishes till you find what works for you.
