        HERE_S_YOUR_MISSION_THEN_YOU_RE_TO                                      = 7776,  -- Here's your mission, then. You're to fight Orcs in the areas around here, and bring me one of their axes as proof.
        IF_YOU_BRING_ME_AN_ORCISH_AXE_WITHOUT                                   = 7777,  -- If you bring me an Orcish Axe without incident, you'll receive a reward as dictated by the laws of the Kingdom of San d'Oria.
        THAT_IS_ALL_YOU_LL_TAKE_THE_MISSION                                     = 7778,  -- That is all. You'll take the mission then?
        ACCEPT_MISSIONH_I_ACCEPT_COULD_YOU_EXPLAIN_AGAIN                        = 7779,  -- Accept missionH I accept. Could you explain again? No thank you, sir.
        BRING_ME_ONE_OF_THOSE_AXES_AND_I                                        = 7780,  -- Bring me one of those axes, and I'll consider the mission a success. No running away now; we've a proud country to defend!
        MADE_IT_BACK_IN_ONE_PIECE_GOOD_A                                        = 7781,  -- Made it back in one piece? Good. A soldier who can't beat an Orc or two is no soldier of San d'Oria!
        LET_S_SEE_THAT_AXE_THEN_I_CAN                                           = 7782,  -- Let's see that axe, then. I can't consider the mission complete without proof.
        MISSION_COMPLETE_NOT_BAD_FOR_A_NEW_RECRUIT                              = 7783,  -- Mission complete. Not bad, for a new recruit. Here's your reward, %.
        WHAT_S_THIS_I_DON_T_RECALL_ASKING                                       = 7784,  -- What's this? I don't recall asking you for one of these! Take it back.
        WHERE_ARE_WE_GETTING_THESE_NEW_RECRUITS                                 = 7785,  -- Where are we getting these new recruits!?
        LISTEN_BEFORE_YOU_BRING_ME_AN_ITEM_YOU                                  = 7786,  -- Listen, before you bring me an item, you must first accept a mission! These are our country's rules, and I'll see you mind them.
        PERSISTENT_AREN_T_YOU_MIND_YOU_THAT_ONE                                 = 7787,  -- Persistent, aren't you? Mind you that one Orc under the belt does not a hero make! Ah, I've just the job for you...
        BAT_PATROL_HOW_ABOUT_IT_SHOULDN_T_BE                                    = 7788,  -- Bat patrol! How about it? Shouldn't be a problem for an adventurer such as yourself!
        HERE_S_YOUR_MISSION_THEN_YOU_RE_TO_2                                    = 7789,  -- Here's your mission, then. You're to rid King Ranperre's Tomb of the bats that lurk there and bring me a fang as proof.
        IF_YOU_BRING_ME_A_BAT_FANG_WITHOUT                                      = 7790,  -- If you bring me a Bat Fang without incident, you'll receive a reward as dictated by the laws of the Kingdom of San d'Oria.
        ONCE_YOU_GET_A_BAT_FANG_BRING_IT                                        = 7791,  -- Once you get a Bat Fang, bring it back to me and I'll consider the mission a success. Oh, and watch out for those skeletons!
        AH_YOU_VE_RETURNED_I_FEARED_THOSE_SKELETONS                             = 7792,  -- Ah, you've returned! I feared those skeletons had gotten a hold of you, I did.
        SO_YOU_VE_BROUGHT_ME_SOMETHING_BACK_FROM                                = 7793,  -- So, you've brought me something back from the bats? I'll need that as proof.
        MISSION_COMPLETE_NOT_BAD_FOR_A_NEW_RECRUIT_2                            = 7794,  -- Mission complete. Not bad, for a new recruit.A Here's your reward, %.
        AH_THE_NEW_RECRUIT_S_BACK_AGAIN_I                                       = 7795,  -- Ah, the new recruit's back again? I'm sorry, but I've no time for you today.
        STILL_HERE_WELL_PERHAPS_YOU_CAN_BE_OF                                   = 7796,  -- Still here? Well, perhaps you can be of some help. There's been a plague of kidnappings of late, and I've no doubt the Ghelsba Orcs are behind it.
        NORMALLY_THE_ROYAL_KNIGHTS_OF_SAN_D_ORIA                                = 7797,  -- Normally, the Royal Knights of San d'Oria would be on the job already, but the two princes that give the orders are at odds.
        PRINCE_TRION_THE_ELDEST_SAYS_WE_SHOULD_LAUNCH                           = 7798,  -- Prince Trion, the eldest, says we should launch a full attack, with all haste.
        WHILE_HIS_YOUNGER_BROTHER_PRINCE_PIEUJE_SAYS_THE                        = 7799,  -- While his younger brother, Prince Pieuje says the safety of the children comes first, and he won't authorize an attack.
        THEY_VE_BEEN_ARGUING_THIS_BACK_AND_FORTH                                = 7800,  -- They've been arguing this back and forth for days. The Knights' hands are tied, and frankly, nobody knows what to do.
        IF_YOU_REALLY_WANT_TO_MAKE_A_NAME                                       = 7801,  -- If you really want to make a name for yourself as an adventurer, go to Ghelsba, and rescue those kidnapped children!
        WHAT_THINK_YOU_WILL_YOU_GO                                              = 7802,  -- What think you? Will you go?
        HERE_S_YOUR_MISSION_THEN_YOU_ARE_TO                                     = 7803,  -- Here's your mission, then. You are to rescue the two children that have been kidnapped bye the Orcs of the Ghelsba Outpost.
        THE_GHELSBA_OUTPOST_IS_TO_THE_NORTHWEST_OF                              = 7804,  -- The Ghelsba Outpost is to the northwest of West Ronfaure. Take the path before the Westgate, then turn right when the path splits in the forest. You'll find the outpost entrance up in the hills.
        ORCS_TEND_TO_KEEP_THEIR_HOSTAGES_IN_TENTS                               = 7805,  -- Orcs tend to keep their hostages in tents or small huts. Once you're inside the compound, check the huts first.
        AH_YOU_VE_RETURNED_YOU_WERE_GONE_SO                                     = 7806,  -- Ah, you've returned! You were gone so long, I feared you'd been had for dinner!
        YOU_MAY_BE_OF_TRUER_METTLE_THAN_I                                       = 7807,  -- You may be of truer mettle than I thought. Mission complete!
        HERE_S_YOUR_REWARD_AND_TO_FURTHER_RECOGNIZE                             = 7808,  -- Here's your reward, %. And to further recognize your accomplishment...
        I_HEREBY_ACKNOWLEDGE_YOU_AS_A_TRUE_ADVENTURER                           = 7809,  -- I hereby acknowledge you, %, as a true Adventurer of San d'Oria! You're now mission rank 2, as well.
        BUT_DON_T_GET_TOO_EXCITED_YOUR_TITLE                                    = 7810,  -- But don't get too excited. Your title only holds clout here in the Kingdom of San d'Oria, understand?
        IN_ORDER_TO_BECOME_A_TRUE_ADVENTURER_AND                                = 7811,  -- In order to become a true Adventurer and bear the Adventurer's Badge, you must be acknowledged as such by the countries of Bastok and Windurst.
        TIS_A_TREATY_BETWEEN_THE_THREE_LANDS_AND                                = 7812,  -- 'Tis a treaty between the three lands, and its word is law. I know it's a pain, but those are the rules.
        FOR_NOW_I_D_RECOMMEND_YOU_CUT_YOUR                                      = 7813,  -- For now, I'd recommend you cut your adventuring teeth in the areas near here. Sooner or later you'll find your way into other lands.
        CLIENT_SENT_SERVER_A_BAD_VALUE                                          = 7814,  -- Client sent server a bad value!
        ID_11MRSX_J_F_SX_B_7I_M_M                                               = 7815,  -- 11Mrsx-%j%F`%sx*"B%7i)M%m)gH"*HB
        AIRSHIPS_FLY_BETWEEN_OUR_KINGDOM_AND_THE_GRAND                          = 7816,  -- Airships fly between our kingdom and the Grand Duchy of Jeuno to the east. I'll never forget the first day I saw one of those ships fly...
        JEUNO_S_HISTORY_IS_SHORT_BUT_QUICKLY_DID                                = 7817,  -- Jeuno's history is short, but quickly did that village of Hume fishermen grow into what it is today.
        WHEN_THEIR_ARCHDUKE_CAME_TO_POWER_HE_EXCAVATED                          = 7818,  -- When their archduke came to power, he excavated the ruins nearby. The knowledge they found there made them as mighty as San d'Oria, by any reckoning.
        BUT_ONCE_A_FISHERMAN_ALWAYS_A_FISHERMAN_I                               = 7819,  -- But once a fisherman, always a fisherman, I say. 'Tis the Elvaan of San d'Oria that will rule Vana'diel, mark my words!
